// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// F3 wave 3 — class-C 1-arg / errno-reloc family. AUTHORS the NEW ptr-arg
// sub-template (chdir/unlink/rmdir, NO leading sxtw, 8-instr 32 B body,
// errno relocs @0x10/0x14) and CLONES the existing close 9-instr 36 B body
// for the int-arg variants (fsync/dup, only the SYS# byte changes vs
// rt_close). All five primitives mirror the runtime.c bodies above:
//   chdir(SYS12)/unlink(SYS10)/rmdir(SYS137)/fsync(SYS95)/dup(SYS41)
// Each is `_hxlcl_syscall1_cf(SYS, arg)` whose clang -O2 emit was verified
// against `as -arch arm64` (see PR description for hex tables). The
// PAGE21/PAGEOFF12 reloc pair targets the SHARED `_hxlcl_errno` UNDEFINED
// external symbol (resolved by ld64 to runtime.c's hxlcl_errno), same as
// rt_close / rt_dup2 / rt_read / rt_write / rt_mkdir / rt_fstat / rt_stat.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// ── rt_chdir (F3 wave 3 — class-C 1-arg PTR + errno-reloc · NEW TEMPLATE) ─
// chdir(const char *path) -> int. The FIRST ptr-arg 1-arg _cf svc-trap:
// path/x0 is already 64-bit (a pointer), so NO leading sxtw — 1 instr
// shorter than rt_close's int-arg shape. 8 instr, 32 B:
//   mov w16,#12 / svc #0x80 / cset x8,hs / cbz x8,Lret
//   / adrp x8,errno / str w0,[x8] / mov x0,#-1 / ret
// errno reloc sites: 0x10 (PAGE21) / 0x14 (PAGEOFF12) — shifted -4 vs
// rt_close because the leading sxtw is absent. SYS_CHDIR = 12. clang -O2
// (== as -arch arm64, in runtime.c's `#define errno hxlcl_errno` context)
